.TH Install-Docker 1 "November 2025" "docker-webhook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
Install-Docker \- Install Docker CE, CLI, containerd, buildx, and compose plugin
.SH SYNOPSIS
Install-Docker [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Installs Docker CE, CLI, containerd, buildx, and compose plugin. Handles removal of conflicting packages. Includes special instructions for ODROID and Raspberry Pi hardware. Supports both Debian and Ubuntu systems. Automatically detects architecture and installs appropriate packages.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.B --no-install-recommends
Install only essential packages, omitting recommended extras.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Show actions without making changes.
.TP
.B --force
Force reinstallation of Docker packages.
.SH USAGE
sudo ./bin/Install-Docker [OPTIONS]
